## Code Style & Standards

### HTML
- Use semantic HTML5 elements (`<header>`, `<nav>`, `<main>`, `<section>`, `<article>`, `<footer>`)
- Include proper meta tags: viewport, description, keywords, Open Graph
- Add descriptive alt text for all images
- Use descriptive ID and class names (BEM methodology preferred)
- Ensure all forms have proper labels and validation attributes
- Include ARIA labels where needed for accessibility

### CSS
- Use CSS custom properties (variables) for colors, spacing, and typography
- Mobile-first responsive design with min-width media queries
- Avoid !important declarations
- Use flexbox and CSS Grid for layouts
- Keep specificity low, avoid deep nesting
- Group related styles together
- Comment major sections

### JavaScript
- Use modern ES6+ syntax
- Keep code modular and reusable
- Use event delegation for better performance
- Avoid global variables, use IIFE or modules
- Add loading states for async operations
- Include error handling for all user interactions

## Performance Guidelines
- Optimize images (WebP format with fallbacks, max 200KB per image)
- Lazy load images below the fold
- Minify CSS and JS for production
- Use system fonts or limit to 2 custom font families
- Inline critical CSS for above-the-fold content
- Defer non-critical JavaScript

## Accessibility Requirements
- WCAG 2.1 Level AA compliance minimum
- Keyboard navigation support for all interactive elements
- Focus indicators visible on all focusable elements
- Color contrast ratio minimum 4.5:1 for text
- Skip navigation links for screen readers
- Proper heading hierarchy (h1-h6)

## SEO Best Practices
- Unique, descriptive title tags (50-60 characters)
- Meta descriptions (150-160 characters)
- Canonical URLs
- Structured data (Schema.org JSON-LD)
- XML sitemap
- Robots.txt file
- Semantic heading structure

## Form Handling
- Client-side validation with HTML5 attributes
- Clear error messages
- Submit button disabled during processing
- Success/error feedback to users
- Honeypot field for spam prevention
- Use Formspree, FormSubmit, or similar for backend

## Browser Support
- Modern browsers (last 2 versions)
- Graceful degradation for older browsers
- Test on Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge

## Naming Conventions
- Files: lowercase with hyphens (about-us.html, main-styles.css)
- Classes: BEM methodology (block__element--modifier)
- IDs: camelCase for JavaScript hooks
- Images: descriptive names (hero-background-office.jpg)

## Comments & Documentation
- Comment complex CSS selectors
- Document JavaScript functions with JSDoc style
- Add TODO comments for future improvements
- Include setup instructions in README.md

## Git Workflow (if using version control)
- Meaningful commit messages
- Feature branches for major changes
- Keep commits atomic and focused
- Use .gitignore for unnecessary files

## Testing Checklist
- Validate HTML (W3C Validator)
- Validate CSS
- Test all forms and interactions
- Check responsive design on multiple devices
- Test page load speed (Google PageSpeed Insights)
- Check accessibility (WAVE, axe DevTools)
- Cross-browser testing
- Spell check all content

## Common Components to Include
- Responsive navigation with mobile menu
